      • expandFolders

        public void expandFolders(String folderPath,
                 String siteName)
        Expands all the folders in the path under specified site.


        1. To expand the site folder node itself set folder path empty. For example:
        expandFolders("", "government");
        expandFolders("", "rijksoverheid");

        2. To expand a specific folder specify path to that folder and site name. For example:
        expandFolders("verzamelingen/bewindspersonen/Mark Rutte", "government");
        expandFolders("government/verzamelingen/bewindspersonen/Mark Rutte", "government");
        Note.The both calls above will result the same - so you can specify leading site folder in the folder path or not.

        Please keep in mind that wrong folders names are not checked.
        Site name cannot be empty or null.

        Parameters:
        folderPath - Path containing folders separated with "/"
        siteName - Site name name

      • collapseFolders

        public void collapseFolders(String folderPath,
                   String siteName)
        Collapses folders in the path under specified site. The method will collapse exactly folders specified in the path (in reverse order). The site folder will not be collapsed automaticaly.


        1. To collapse the site folder set folder path empty. For example:
        collapseFolders("", "government");
        collapseFolders("", "rijksoverheid");

        2. To collapse specific folder(s) specify path to that folder(s) and site name.
        Example 1.
        collapseFolders("verzamelingen/bewindspersonen/Mark Rutte", "rijksoverheid");
        The folders will be collapsed in order 'Mark Rutte', 'bewindspersonen', and 'verzamelingen'. The site folder 'rijksoverheid' will not be collapsed.
        Example 2.
        collapseFolders("bewindspersonen", "rijksoverheid");
        Only the folder 'bewindspersonen' will be collapsed independend on opened or closed folders under the bewindspersonen. The site folder 'rijksoverheid' will not.

        Please keep in mind that wrong folders names are not checked.
        Site name cannot be empty or null.

        Parameters:
        folderPath - Path containing folders separated with "/"
        siteName - Site name name
